      <description>"Frank L. ""Dusty"" Rhoades was born in Shreveport, La., and attended the
            Louisiana Polytechnic Institute before enlisting in the Army Air Corps at the start of
            World War II. He served as a bomber pilot flying a B-24 ""Liberator."" He graduated from
            the Louisiana Polytechnic Institute and the University of Oklahoma and worked a variety
            of positions in the natural gas, aircraft, and petroleum engineering
            fields."</description>
