   <abstract xlink:href="http://lib.lsu.edu/services/oralhistory/abstracts/military/Rhoades_Frank.abs.pdf">Rhoades discusses his family and education; attending Louisiana Polytechnic
            Institute; his training as an aircraft engineer and pilot; bombing missions over Germany
            flown from his base in northern England; his work in natural gas engineering in South
            Louisiana; owning a machine shop in Bossier City, La.; working for an ordnance plant
            near Minden, La.; his jobs in aircraft construction; his work in petroleum pipeline
            engineering in Texas, Alaska, and Saudi Arabia; and Saudi Arabian cultural
            customs.</abstract>
